cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and discourse relation classification. Additionally, the use of neural networks and adversarial training suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus on feature extraction and classification also suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of connectives and salient features could also suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
